Like this?  Yes, there you go,

00:13:59.000 --> 00:14:06.000
like that.  Right.
Because there is an inflection point

00:14:06.000 --> 00:14:14.000
here, right?  So,
this is what's sometimes called the

00:14:14.000 --> 00:14:21.000
optimum yield,
